gomodel:SYNGO_2749  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Background: this paper reports on the non-conventional role of postsynaptic Nrxn1; neurexin 1 beta in negatively regulating the ability to induce presynaptic differentiation of neuroligin 1.\n\nFig.3: \"cis-expression of neurexins reduces synaptogenic activity of neuroligin-1 in hippocampal neurons\"\nFig.4: \"cis-expressed neurexins directly block synaptogenic activity of neuroligin-1\"\nFig.5: \"β-Neurexin overexpression results in upregulation of neuroligins in cis\"\nFig.6: \"Dendritic neurexin expression reduces vGlut1 clustering and neurexin binding in dissociated hippocampal neurons\". Experimental description: - The species of overexpressed neurexin 1 beta protein isnot stated in the paper. Authors were contacted (dd. 2/3/2018, peter.scheiffele@unibas.ch). Answer was:\n\n\"Hi Pim\nthe transgenic mice expressed a mouse Nrx1beta isoform\nBest,\nPeter\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2749" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

